I'm italian, and this is not how Italy looks like.
These are stereotypes summarized.
The music, the people, the dresses... not the reality.
The market is similar to the reality, but not the rest.
Don't expect Italy to be a quiet and harmonious place, beacuse it isn't.
There will always be background hum, screams, annoying noises ...
Ordinary people don't dress well, only a few are elegant.
Food: some restaurants suck.
However, it is true, we are the land of engines. We have the famous 'motor valley' where I live. Visit this area rather!
